article.headline: Navy 71, Army 63
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Adam Teague scored 18 points and grabbed 11 rebounds, leading Navy to a 71-63 win over Army in Patriot League basketball Saturday. Cliff Colbert scored 17 points for Navy. Chris Harris added 11, and Greg Sprink grabbed a game-high 12 rebounds for the Midshipmen. Navy (15-12, 8-4) scored 53 points, 30 of them from beyond the arc, in the second half to overcome a nine-point halftime deficit. Army (11-15, 4-8) led 27-18 at intermission, but the Midshipmen shot 58.6 percent from the floor to outscore the Black Knights, 53-36, in the second stanza. Jarell Brown led the Black Knights with 18 points. Josh Miller added 14 points, five rebounds, six assists and four steals. Cleveland Richard was the third Army player in double figures with 10. Navy shot 39.7 percent from the floor overall and made 11-of-29 of its three-point shots. Army was 41.9 percent from the floor and was 7-of-26 from beyond the arc.
